"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:11.6\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">11.6</span> Money</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">The relative values of monetary units mentioned in the New Testament may best be understood in their relationship to the denarius, which was equivalent to one day’s wages for a common laborer:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>Talent = 6,000 denarii; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:24\">MAT 18:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:15\">MAT 25:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:16\">MAT 25:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:20\">MAT 25:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:20\">MAT 25:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:20\">MAT 25:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:20\">MAT 25:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:22\">MAT 25:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:22\">MAT 25:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:22\">MAT 25:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:24\">MAT 25:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:25\">MAT 25:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:28\">MAT 25:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:28\">MAT 25:28</a></p>\n<p>Mina = 1,000 denarii; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:13\">LUK 19:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:16\">LUK 19:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:16\">LUK 19:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:18\">LUK 19:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:18\">LUK 19:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:20\">LUK 19:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:24\">LUK 19:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:24\">LUK 19:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:25\">LUK 19:25</a></p>\n<p>Stater = 4 denarii; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:27\">MAT 17:27</a></p>\n<p>Didrachma = 2 denarii; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:24\">MAT 17:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:24\">MAT 17:24</a></p>\n<p>Denarius (also Drachma) = ONE DAY’S WAGE; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:28\">MAT 18:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:2\">MAT 20:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:9\">MAT 20:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:10\">MAT 20:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:13\">MAT 20:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:19\">MAT 22:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:37\">MRK 6:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:15\">MRK 12:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:5\">MRK 14:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:41\">LUK 7:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:35\">LUK 10:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:8\">LUK 15:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:8\">LUK 15:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:9\">LUK 15:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:24\">LUK 20:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:7\">JHN 6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:5\">JHN 12:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:6\">REV 6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:6\">REV 6:6</a></p>\n<p>Assarion = 1/16 denarius; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:29\">MAT 10:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:6\">LUK 12:6</a></p>\n<p>Kodrantes = 1/64 denarius; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:26\">MAT 5:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:42\">MRK 12:42</a></p>\n<p>Lepton = 1/128 denarius; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:42\">MRK 12:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:59\">LUK 12:59</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:2\">LUK 21:2</a></p>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">For a general discussion of translating terms related to money, see <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">1.6.3 Money, coins&lt;REALIA:1.6.3&gt;</a>.</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>maneh: See <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">11.2.2 Mina&lt;REALIA:11.2.2&gt;</a>, “Mina.”</p>\n<p>talanton: See <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">11.2.3 Talent&lt;REALIA:11.2.3&gt;</a>, “Talent.”</p>\n<p>peres: See <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">11.1.4 Peres, Parsin&lt;REALIA:11.1.4&gt;</a>, “Peres, Parsin.”</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
